name: Strike Anywhere screenprinted gigposter
description:
This is a screenprinted gigposter created for Strike Anywhere's performance at Champion Ship in Lemoyne, PA in June of 2009. The artwork features good old George Washington, who is from Virginia, just like Strike Anywhere. It is a limited edition of 50, signed and numbered by the artist.

This is a 2 color print on heavy gray paper. The poster measures 8.5" x 17".

Poster will be safely shipped in a heavy duty tube.

name: Title Fight and This is Hell screenprinted gigposter
description:
This is a screenprinted gigposter created for Title Fight and This is Hell's performance at the Talking Head Club in Baltimore, MD in June of 2009. The skyline featured on teh poster is that of Baltimore. It is a limited edition of 43, signed and numbered by the artist.

This is a 3 color print on heavy gray paper. The poster measures 13" x 17".

Poster will be safely shipped in a heavy duty tube.

name: Paint It Black screenprinted gigposter
description:
This is a screenprinted gigposter created for Paint it Black's performance at Champion Ship in Lemoyne, PA in April of 2009. It is a limited edition of 50, signed and numbered by the artist. This poster features Philly's sons of hardcore and father of liberty, Ben Frankiln.

This is a one color print with black spray paint stenciled lettering on French Press 100 lb Natural Speckletone paper. Each poster is unique.

Poster will be safely shipped in a heavy duty tube.

name: Set Your Goals/Four Year Strong Screenprinted gigposter
description:
This is a screenprinted gigposter created for Set Your Goals and Four Year Strong's performance at the Ottobar in Baltimore, MD in July of 2009. It is a limited edition of 70, signed and numbered by the artist.

This is a 3 color print on French Press Berrylicious paper. There is a hand splattered orange spray paint background making each poster unique.

Poster will be safely shipped in a heavy duty tube.

name: I Know You're Strong screenprinted cat poster
description:
This is a 2 color print with handpainted white details on the eyes. Printed on 12.5" x 9" French Gumdrop Green paper, signed and numbered out on 100.

This is a quote from the Weakerthans song "A Plea From a Cat Named Virtue". The print was created for the Lyrically Speaking show at Singed and Numbered Gallery in Salt Lake City, UT.
